  <front>
   <head>A POEM on the Princess Amelia. In Answer to Damon, who invited the Nymphs of Bath, to sing her Praise.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">calls, I lead the Way;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ye Nymphs of , come, aid my Lay,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Come, strike the trembling String:</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Name so sweetly flows,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her Face such wond'rous Goodness shows,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Who can refuse to sing?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Presence, like the Sun benign,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sheds Blessings where she deigns to shine;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And brightens all the Place.</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But when the Goddess disappears,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Our drooping Heads and Eyes in Tears</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Will witness our Distress.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">wou'd the Muses aid my Wing,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">tune my Voice to sing!</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">I'd take the lovely Theme.</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Name the Vale shou'd fill,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And echo back from Hill to Hill;</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Sweet as her rising Fame.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">envious Foes in vain repine,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">May , blest in  Line,</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Still  Balance sway!</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Till Plenty, Liberty and Peace</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Shall fill the World â€” till Faction cease,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Earth resound the Joy.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
